evel than it.  <br>
<br>
We are talking about the same Everquest where the highest level pet is 49 yet some mobs are rumored to exceed 70 and many more commonly attacked monsters are over 59. Meaning the level difference between monster and and pet trivializes or nullifies any damage done.  The same Everquest where pets have a 60% haste cap.  The same Everquest where our Epic Pet arguably the hardest Epic in the game hits for a maximum of 81 and yet there are DireCharmable creatures in recent expansion zones where 60th level characters can get xp that will hit for 140 have no haste cap and double the epic pets hit points.<br>
<br>
I hear all the time how &quot;My Pet beats many melees in damage on raids.&quot;  Never has that been my experience, ever.  Furthermore the mechanics of the game make that simply impossible.  Certainly if that player controlled melee is specifically not trying to draw aggro, does not want to die for the x-teenth time this encounter, or is too busy carrying on other chat to fight all out, then yes the pet will beat that melee.  But straight damage per second?  That isn't possible.  The pet's level is too low, the pet's attack rating is too low, the pet's haste cap is too low, the pet's maximum damage per hit is too low, and some discussion is active that pet procs and spells are completely inactive against a creature that is 63+ yet that will not stop the pet from trying.  Wasting valuable time to cast and further lowering its DPS in the process.<br>
<br>
I completely understand that some will carry a cheery attitude regardless because they play EQ and thier magicians to have fun.  Good for you!  More power to you!  Our community needs people like you.  But WAKE UP!  Planes of Power is coming!  We are a low damage nuisance to end game creatures now.  We will be an obsolete joke when that expansion hits the shelves.  An upgrade in melee pet damage from 67 to 81 is MEANINGLESS to a monster that has one million hit points.  I'm sure the Thought Horror Overfiend is terrified he'll be the target of an all mage onslaught...  I play to have fun too, and Pre-Kunark my magician was fun.  Now he's a vending machine camped near the bazaar that I truly wish was powerful enough to bring to an game encounter so that the fun I had with him in the past doesn't remain in the past.<br>
<br>
Face the facts and they are undisputable.  Pet level at 49 is too low to be effective.  Pet Melee damage max at 81 is trivial.  Pet haste cap at 60% maximum is a handicap.  Low damage and often resisted pet spells are a waste of the pet's already minimal effort.<br>
